 false, "description": "Area: All kinds of macros (custom derive, macro_rules!, proc macros, ..)"}, {"id": 650731663, "node_id": "MDU6TGFiZWw2NTA3MzE2NjM=", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/labels/C-bug", "name": "C-bug", "color": "f5f1fd", "default": false, "description": "Category: This is a bug."}, {"id": 2079070889, "node_id": "MDU6TGFiZWwyMDc5MDcwODg5", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/labels/A-proc-macros", "name": "A-proc-macros", "color": "f7e101", "default": false, "description": "Area: Procedural macros"}], "state": "closed", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 1, "created_at": "2020-08-26T02:13:02Z", "updated_at": "2020-09-01T22:03:36Z", "closed_at": "2020-09-01T22:03:36Z", "author_association": "MEMBER", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "The following code (repository at https://github.com/Aaron1011/derive-bug):\r\n\r\n```rust\r\n// lib.rs\r\nuse proc_macro::TokenStream;\r\n\r\n#[proc_macro_derive(MyDerive)]\r\npub fn my_derive(input: TokenStream) -> TokenStream {\r\n    println!(\"Derive input: {}\", input);\r\n    TokenStream::new()\r\n}\r\n\r\n\r\n// main.rs\r\n\r\n#[derive(derive_bug::MyDerive)]\r\nstruct Foo<#[cfg(FALSE)] T> {\r\n    #[cfg(FALSE)] field: T,\r\n    val: String,\r\n    array: [u8; {\r\n        #[cfg(FALSE)] struct Bar;\r\n        0\r\n    }]\r\n}\r\n\r\nfn main() {}\r\n```\r\n\r\nproduces the following output:\r\n\r\n```\r\nDerive input: struct Foo < #[cfg(FALSE)] T > { val : String, array : [u8 ; { 0 }], }\r\n```\r\n\r\nNote how all `#[cfg(FALSE)]` targets are stripped, except for the generic parameter `T`. This seems quite inconsistent.\r\n\r\nTested on `rustc 1.47.0-nightly (de521cbb3 2020-08-21)`", "closed_by": {"login": "bors", "id": 3372342, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjMzNzIzNDI=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/3372342?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/bors", "html_url": "https://github.com/bors"